  "text": {
    "content-type": "text/html",
    "data": "<p>Collections are 'virtual folders' that contain content objects based on criteria. Those criteria can be</p>&#13;\n<ul>&#13;\n<li>type of content</li>&#13;\n<li>subject, or tag</li>&#13;\n<li>a variety of time-based criteria</li>&#13;\n<li>based on certain text</li>&#13;\n<li>based on who created them</li>&#13;\n<li>and a whole range of other metadata</li>&#13;\n</ul>&#13;\n<p>And, of course, you can combine all of them to narrow down your selection.</p>&#13;\n<p>Richtext</p>&#13;\n<p>They also come with a richtext introduction, meaning the introduction can contain formatting, <a href=\"https://docs.plone.org/working-with-content/using-collections/newstyle/creating_collections.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" title=\"Link to the Plone docs on creating collections\">links</a> and images</p>&#13;\n<p><img src=\"http://localhost:8080/Plone/testcases/midsummer.jpg/@@images/fd5b4cc3-a2d9-43f1-9b55-f214691041ed.jpeg\" title=\"How to lure people to Finland\" alt=\"A meme enticing people to come to Finland to sprint on Plone\" class=\"image-inline\"/></p>",
    "encoding": "utf-8"
